# Daily Diary - Day 08

## Object-Oriented Programming Basics

### Today's Topics
- Classes and Objects
- Instance Variables vs Local Variables
- Methods in Classes
- Object Creation and Usage
- Basic OOP Principles

### Practical Work
- Created multiple classes with attributes and methods
- Instantiated objects and called methods
- Implemented real-world entities as classes
- Practiced encapsulation basics

### Code Example
```java
// Class definition
class Student {
    // Instance variables
    String name;
    int age;
    double marks;
    
    // Method
    public void displayInfo() {
        System.out.println("Name: " + name);
        System.out.println("Age: " + age);
        System.out.println("Marks: " + marks);
    }
    
    public boolean isPassed() {
        return marks >= 40;
    }
}

public class OOPDemo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Object creation
        Student student1 = new Student();
        student1.name = "Alice";
        student1.age = 20;
        student1.marks = 85.5;
        
        student1.displayInfo();
        System.out.println("Passed: " + student1.isPassed());
    }
}
